[SN]TITLE[SN]
Callum Braley: Gloucester scrum-half signs new deal with Premiership club

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Gloucester scrum-half Callum Braley has signed a new contract extension for the 2017-18 season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 22-year-old former Bristol player has been with the Cherry and Whites since the summer of 2014.
"I'm very excited to be staying at the club," the former England Under-20 international told Gloucester's club website.
"I owe it a lot for helping me progress my career and I'm looking forward to seeing what the future holds here."
